The paper focuses on detecting dense subgraphs in bipartite graphs, which is a core component in many applications such as social network mining, bioinformatics, and fraud detection. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also discusses the application of the proposed algorithm in fraud detection, which falls under the categories of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of multiple features and the reduction of feature engineering, which relates to cs.SOC (Social and Information Networks) and cs.DB (Databases).
